## PolySyncIterable.toMap() method

Return a `Map` made from the entries of `this`<!-- -->. This method is roughly equivalent to calling `new Map(iter.toArray())`<!-- -->.

**Signature:**

```typescript
toMap<K, V>(this: PolySyncIterable<[K, V] | readonly [K, V]>): Map<K, V>;
```

|  Parameter | Type | Description |
|  --- | --- | --- |
|  this | [PolySyncIterable](./polyethylene.polysynciterable.md)<!-- -->&lt;\[K, V\] \| readonly \[K, V\]&gt; |  |

**Returns:**

Map&lt;K, V&gt;

A `Map` composed of the entries yielded by this iterable.

## Remarks

This method is only available for iterations of pairs.
